Class JobApplication

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.nhqml.iwillgetajob.db.JobApplication

  • public class JobApplication
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a Job Application. This class also provides multiple functions to get / set values.

    • Field Detail

      • id

        private long id
        Attribute used by the database as Primary Key

      • step

        private int step
        The step of the the JobApplication. (0) = I will apply (1) = I have applied (2) = I have called again (3) = I have an interview

      • jobTitle

        private java.lang.String jobTitle
        The title of the job you apply.

      • companyName

        private java.lang.String companyName
        The company name.

      • dates

        private final java.time.ZonedDateTime[] dates
        An array of dates corresponding to the dates you (will apply / applied / called again / have a interview). Date of each step is stored in dates[step].

      • contact

        private final JobApplication.Contact contact
        The JobApplication.Contact object. Contains all the information about your contact in the company.

      • jobRef

        private java.lang.String jobRef
        The reference of the job (e.g. a link to the website on which you found the job).

      • notes

        private java.lang.String notes
        Any notes about this JobApplication.

      • JAComparatorTitleAZ

        public static final java.util.Comparator<JobApplication> JAComparatorTitleAZ
        Compare jobTitle attribute. This is case insensitive. Alphabetical order.

      • JAComparatorTitleZA

        public static final java.util.Comparator<JobApplication> JAComparatorTitleZA
        Compare jobTitle attribute. This is case insensitive. Reverse alphabetical order.

      • JAComparatorTitleDate

        public static final java.util.Comparator<JobApplication> JAComparatorTitleDate
        Compare dates[step] attribute. Chronological order (12/01/1990 < 18/06/2001). If dates are equals, comparison is done with JAComparatorTitleAZ
